CDC Director Dr. Tom Frieden meets with Donka hospital nurse Claire Tchecola in Guinea. She is one of the few survivors who has made her story public and continues educating others about Ebola, even though she and her family have been stigmatized for it. 
Learn more about CDC’s role in the Ebola response on the Road to Zero: link in bio.

results.name: Meet NCEH/ATSDR senior health scientist, Chinaro Kennedy, DPH. As a senior clearance officer, she ensures the accuracy of environmental health scientific documents before they are released to the public. One of Dr. Kennedy’s main contributions to public health was participating on a study that looked the impact of lead laws to prevent lead poisoning among small children. results.name: People of all genders, ages, and ethnicities can be at risk for suicide but some groups are at higher risk than others. Men are about four times more likely than women to die from suicide. However, women are more likely to express suicidal thoughts and to make nonfatal attempts than men.
